comment: *there are a couple high-ish thresholds but otherwise wheelchair accessible* Cafe is open seasonally (closes mid-October, opens again in spring). Origins is a beautiful, mid price cafe / restaurant in a greenhouse. I greatly enjoyed the plants, live music, locally sourced food and beautiful crafts from around the world for sale!

name: AD Bruce Religion Center
directions: second floor
comment: men's and women's single stall; "Because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice. For those preferring more privacy, we are providing the following information." Learn more at: http://www.uh.edu/lgbtq/transgender_affairs/

name: Lamar Fleming Jr. Building, room 225
directions: Second floor
comment: It is a single stall marked male. "Because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice. For those preferring more privacy, we are providing the following information." Learn more at: http://www.uh.edu/lgbtq/transgender_affairs/

name: UH Women's, Gender, & Sexuality Studies Department/Agnes Arnold Hall 624
directions: You can go to room 624 (WGSS Department) during open hours and ask for a key to use the multi-stall faculty restroom on the 6th floor. Otherwise, all restrooms in the Agnes Arnold Hall Building are gendered multi-stall and/or hard to access. The department also provides private space for chestfeeding/breastfeeding if you need that. For help finding the building, use https://uh.edu/maps/.
comment: In addition to family/unisex/single stall restrooms, because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice, including gendered multi-stall restrooms, if they are comfortable doing so.

name: Blaffer Art Museum/UH Fine Arts Building
directions: Located on the 2nd floor (Blaffer Gallery). For help finding the building, use their website at http://blafferartmuseum.org/visit/ or https://uh.edu/maps/.
comment: Admission to the museum is free. Parking information is on their website at http://blafferartmuseum.org/visit/ . In addition to family/unisex/single stall restrooms, because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice, including gendered multi-stall restrooms, if they are comfortable doing so.

name: UH Technology Annex
directions: Room 119 is a "Women's" single stall restroom and room 119A is a "Men's" single stall restroom. For help finding the building, use https://uh.edu/maps/.
comment: In addition to family/unisex/single stall restrooms, because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice, including gendered multi-stall restrooms, if they are comfortable doing so.

name: Playa Bowls
directions: On your left right next to door from parking lot. Very visible & gendered to everyone however it is accessible and single stall. Staff are teenagers who are nice

name: UH Garrison Gym
directions: Single stall family restroom, room 105B. For help finding the building, use https://www.uh.edu/maps/.
comment: In addition to family/unisex/single stall restrooms, because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice, including gendered multi-stall restrooms, if they are comfortable doing so.

name: UH Farish Hall
directions: Restroom is in room 206, you must obtain the key from the UH College of Education in room 214 to access. Only available when the department is open.
comment: In addition to family/unisex/single stall restrooms, because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice, including gendered multi-stall restrooms, if they are comfortable doing so.

name: UH Campus Recreation and Wellness Center
directions: This is the "Family Changing Room." Turn left after the entrance on the first floor. Walk towards the regular locker/changing rooms, then, once you're in front of the regular locker/changing rooms, make another left toward the swimming pool, and the Family Changing Room will be on the left.
comment: In addition to single stall/family restrooms at UH, because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice if you feel comfortable doing so. There are two more ADA Accessible gendered multi-stall restrooms on the first floor if you turn right after the entrance, they're in a secluded hallway.

name: Subway
directions: In the far right corner of the restaurant, down a short hallway. You have to walk across the dining room to access them, but the doors on the front of the restaurant are at the left and right corners, so you could go through the doors on the right to avoid people.

name: Marfreless
comment: This is an upscale bar that has no sign in front. Just the iconic blue door under a fire escape. I suspect you must be a paying customer.

comment: May not be always open, or available for public use during paid events.

name: Mochas coffeehouse
directions: Two bathrooms, both single stall and gender neutral!

name: cam

name: Jack in the Box

comment: There is no "custmers only" sign, but it's sort of implied by the door code. Best to browse or buy something cheap or talk to employees about pet products and care, as though you were looking to buy something and needed some information  first.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Right side of store towards back

name: Urban Ecology Center - Menomonee Valley Branch
directions: First floor restroom at is a single stall, locked door. Urban Ecology Center has a strict policy of self choice in their gendered bathrooms. Staff are instructed to never question anyone for the use of the bathroom of their choice. If you have a negative experience, please tell the Branch Manager or Visitor Services staff.

name: Urban Ecology Center
directions: Second floor restrooms at Riverside Park branch are single stall, locked door. Urban Ecology Center has a strict policy of self choice in their gendered bathrooms. Staff are instructed to never question anyone for the use of the bathroom of their choice. If you have a negative experience, please tell the Branch Manager or Visitor Services staff.

name: Imagine Cafe Vegan Restaurant
directions: Past counter
comment: Both bathrooms are unisex and single stalled.

name: Pro Photo Supply
directions:
PPS is a camera store. Bathroom available for customers (but see comment below). When you walk in, you'll pass an office and a staircase on your right. Right after the staircase (opposite the front register) is an unlabeled brown door, bathroom is through the door and directly back. 
There is an accessible bathroom, but you'll have to specifically ask an employee to let you in to that one.
comment: There is no official customers only policy; it is unlikely to go noticed if you go in only to use the bathroom, but you can just browse a bit if you feel awkward about it.

name: Urgent care bathrooms

directions: it’s by urgent care just ask the information desk

name: Subway

comment: It is a restaurant, might be best if you were already planning to get something to eat or drink before attempting to walk in and use the restroom.

name: 7 Eleven
directions: Bathroom is in the NW corner of the store (closest to the parking lot rather than Millikan Way). There is a door on the North side of the building not far from the bathroom that allows you to access the bathroom wiyhout having to walk past the cashier. It is visible from the counter, though, so you might be greeted. Bathroom down a short hall, it isn't marked.

name: Winnipeg public library
